---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About - TUKE Knowledge Management Demo"
  description="Learn how this website was built through AI conversation using a multi-agent system in a single session."
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-16">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
        Built by AI Conversation
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
        A meta-demonstration of knowledge management principles
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-epistemology/10 to-methodology/10 rounded-xl p-8 mb-12 border-l-4 border-epistemology">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-0 mb-4">The Meta-Nature of This Project</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-0">
          This talk and website about knowledge management was itself created through knowledge management.
          It demonstrates the very principles it teaches - not as abstract theory, but as a working system
          built in real-time through structured AI collaboration.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">How It Was Built</h2>

      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Multi-Agent Architecture</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        Rather than a single AI assistant attempting to build everything sequentially, this project
        employed a <strong>parallel multi-agent system</strong>. Eleven specialized agents worked
        simultaneously during a single conversation session:
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-12 not-prose">
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 shadow-md border-l-4 border-epistemology">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Agent 1: Foundation</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Project structure, configuration, dependencies</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 shadow-md border-l-4 border-methodology">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Agent 2: Glossary Data</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">40 interconnected term definitions with metadata</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 shadow-md border-l-4 border-practice">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Agent 3: Glossary Pages</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Dynamic routes and wiki-style term pages</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 shadow-md border-l-4 border-philosophy">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Agent 4-6: Slide Variants</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Three presentation styles (minimal, ideas, detailed)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 shadow-md border-l-4 border-epistemology">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Agent 7: Components</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Vue components for navigation and interactivity</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 shadow-md border-l-4 border-methodology">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Agent 8: Books Integration</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Reference library with 8 key works</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 shadow-md border-l-4 border-practice">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Agent 9: Deployment</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Final polish, workflows, and documentation</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 shadow-md border-l-4 border-philosophy">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Agent 10: Build & Test</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Verification and production build</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Built in One Session</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The entire website - from initial configuration to deployment-ready state - was created
        in a <strong>single conversation</strong>. This demonstrates:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-8 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li>How AI can orchestrate complex, multi-part projects</li>
        <li>The power of parallel task execution vs. sequential development</li>
        <li>That comprehensive documentation can emerge alongside implementation</li>
        <li>Knowledge management as practice, not just theory</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-4">Demonstrating Its Own Concepts</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-6">
        The glossary contains the very concepts used to build this system:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-none space-y-3 mb-8 not-prose">
        <li>
          <a href="/glossary/tacit-knowledge" class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-epistemology/5 transition-colors">
            <span class="text-2xl">üí°</span>
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold text-epistemology">Tacit Knowledge</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">The AI agents coordinate through implicit patterns, not just explicit instructions</div>
            </div>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/glossary/knowledge-graph" class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-methodology/5 transition-colors">
            <span class="text-2xl">üîó</span>
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold text-methodology">Knowledge Graph</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">Terms interconnect, creating emergent understanding beyond individual definitions</div>
            </div>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/glossary/paradigm-shift" class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-philosophy/5 transition-colors">
            <span class="text-2xl">üîÑ</span>
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold text-philosophy">Paradigm Shift</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">AI-assisted development represents a new paradigm in software creation</div>
            </div>
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="/glossary/double-loop-learning" class="flex items-start gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-practice/5 transition-colors">
            <span class="text-2xl">üîÅ</span>
            <div>
              <div class="font-semibold text-practice">Double-Loop Learning</div>
              <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">The system questions its own assumptions and adjusts strategies mid-build</div>
            </div>
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Technology Stack</h2>
      <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8 not-prose">
        <dl class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <dt class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Astro 5</dt>
            <dd class="text-gray-700">Static site generation with partial hydration. Only ship JavaScript where needed.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Vue 3</dt>
            <dd class="text-gray-700">Interactive components using Composition API. Type-safe with TypeScript.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">Tailwind CSS 4</dt>
            <dd class="text-gray-700">Utility-first styling with custom design tokens for semantic color categories.</dd>
          </div>
          <div>
            <dt class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">GitHub Pages</dt>
            <dd class="text-gray-700">Free hosting for static sites with custom domains and automatic deployments.</dd>
          </div>
        </dl>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">What Makes This Unique</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
        <div class="border-l-4 border-epistemology pl-6">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">It's Reflexive</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            A knowledge management system that documents the knowledge management principles
            used to create it. The medium is the message.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-methodology pl-6">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">It's Multi-Modal</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Same content presented three ways (minimal/ideas/detailed) acknowledges that
            different people learn differently. No single "correct" format.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-practice pl-6">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">It's Interconnected</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Not a linear document but a web of related concepts. Follow your curiosity through
            the knowledge graph.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="border-l-4 border-philosophy pl-6">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">It's Practical</h4>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Not just theory - you can fork this repository, modify the content, and deploy
            your own knowledge base in minutes.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Acknowledgments</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        This project synthesizes ideas from many thinkers:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-8 text-gray-700 space-y-2">
        <li><strong>Michael Polanyi</strong> - Tacit knowledge and the limits of codification</li>
        <li><strong>Thomas Kuhn</strong> - Paradigm shifts and incommensurability</li>
        <li><strong>Jiddu Krishnamurti</strong> - Freedom from accumulated knowledge</li>
        <li><strong>Jon Kabat-Zinn</strong> - Mindfulness attitudes in knowledge work</li>
        <li><strong>Robert Kegan</strong> - Adult development and self-transforming mind</li>
        <li><strong>Jim Collins</strong> - Organizational knowledge architecture</li>
        <li><strong>Chris Argyris</strong> - Double-loop learning and learning disabilities</li>
        <li><strong>Martin Seligman</strong> - Learned optimism and explanatory styles</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-epistemology/10 via-methodology/10 to-practice/10 rounded-xl p-8 text-center not-prose">
        <p class="text-lg text-gray-800 mb-6 font-medium">
          Built with <a href="https://claude.ai" class="text-epistemology hover:underline">Claude</a> by Anthropic
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 justify-center">
          <a
            href="/glossary"
            class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-2 bg-epistemology text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-epistemology/90 transition-colors"
          >
            Explore the Glossary
          </a>
          <a
            href="/slides/minimal/1"
            class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-2 bg-methodology text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-methodology/90 transition-colors"
          >
            View the Slides
          </a>
          <a
            href="/books"
            class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-2 bg-practice text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-practice/90 transition-colors"
          >
            Browse the Books
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
